%pyspark
import os
import requests 
import json
import pprint as pp
root_url = 'http://skiltestc1.southcentralus.cloudapp.azure.com:9008'
url      = os.path.join(root_url, "login")
payload  = {'userId': 'admin', 'password': 'Skymind'}
headers  = {'content-type': 'application/json'}
response = requests.post(url, data=json.dumps(payload), headers=headers)
token    = json.loads(response.text)['token']

import pandas as pd  #pd.io.json.json_normalize()
url = os.path.join(root_url, "deployments")
headers = {'accept': 'application/json',
           'Authorization': 'Bearer {}'.format(token)}
response = requests.request("GET", url, headers=headers)
dat      = json.loads(response.text)
pp.pprint(dat, indent=4)
